    <div class="msg-box">How I Got Started</div>
    <p>As a kid I was always fascinated with visual sensations. I would spend my time scouring over art books, websites, comic books, TV shows, and video games. I wanted to share what I loved about these visual sensations with as many people as I could. As such, art seemed like the best avenue for that.</p>
    <p>I grew up playing with my mother's copy of Dreamweaver as a little kid (back when it was still a Macromedia product), and that sparked my initial interest in web development. I started off with an introductory class in web design at Boston University, but it would take a few years of doing visual development/graphic design work before I tried to truly dip my feet into the web development waters. At one point I took an online course through Rutger's University, and eventually made my way over to DigitalCrafts' Full-Stack program in the fall of 2018.</p>
    <p>I've learned a tremendous amount about the world wide web and its many technologies over the year, and my only desire is to be able to continue learning and growing throughout my career.</p>
